Next Steps

Assign proper sudo privileges to user

Configure SSH access

Document networking configuration

Transition system toward server-style usage

Replicate setup on a cloud VM



---

üîΩ Commands Used (Step-by-Step)

This section lists all commands executed, in the order they were used.


---

Switch to TTY

Ctrl + Alt + F3


---

Login as user

Username: sysadmin
Password: ********


---

Attempt sudo (failed)

sudo apt update

Error:

sysadmin is not in the sudoers file


---

Switch to root user

su -


---

Test GNOME Terminal

gnome-terminal

Result:

Terminal exited immediately



---

Reinstall GNOME Terminal packages

apt install --reinstall gnome-terminal gnome-terminal-data libvte-2.91-0 -y


---

Exit root

exit


---

Reset GNOME configuration

dconf reset -f /org/gnome/terminal/
dconf reset -f /org/gnome/


---

Install alternative terminal

sudo apt install xterm -y


---

Launch xterm from GUI

Alt + F2
xterm


---

Result

xterm opened successfully

Commands executed normally

System confirmed healthy



